radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is fluid-filled with wall hyperenhancement and measures approximately 10 mm. There is a small amount of surrounding fat stranding. Visualized lung bases are clear; the heart is normal in size. No focal lesions in the liver, pancreas, and kidneys. No evidence of intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation. Normal gallbladder. No hydronephrosis; normal ureters. The small and large bowel are normal without evidence of wall thickening. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy.
